item.description:
arXiv:2503.12398v2 Announce Type: replace Abstract: We investigate the exclusive semilpetonic decays of $\Lambda^{+}_{c}	o (\Lambda/n) \ell^{+} 
u_{\ell}~(\ell=e,\mu)$ within the standard model by using the light-front quark model (LFQM). The form factor behaviors are obtained from the effective treatment of nonvalence contributions in addition to the valence ones in the Drell-Yan-West frame due to the Bethe-Salpeter formalism. Based on these form factors, we find that the decay branching ratios of $\Lambda^{+}_{c}	o (\Lambda e^{+} 
u_{e},\,\Lambda \mu^{+} 
u_{e} ,\, n e^{+} 
u_{e},\, n \mu^{+} 
u_{e})$ are about $ (3.39,\,3.21,\,0.36,\,0.35)\%$ with the non-valence contributions, which are consistent with the recent experimental measurements at BESIII. Furthermore, we use the experimental data to fit the $ eta$ parameters in the baryonic distribution amplitudes under the LFQM, resulting in ($ eta_{\Lambda_{c}}, eta_{\Lambda},  eta_{n})= (0.58\pm0.08, 0.52\pm0.08,0.44\pm0.04)$.
